region.name: Capital
region.notes: NV - 19OCT2021 - Region 028 name change from Greater Victoria to Capital.

charities.name: Capacity Building for Supportive Housing Program
charities.description: The Centre offers supportive housing through one‐year renewable leases (for up to 3 years) for 2 populations: 1) women (and their children) escaping domestic violence and 2) refugee and immigrant families. Services assist families in accessing community resources, working through challenges and personal issues, negotiating the legal system and other support to make healthy and productive choices around housing, employment, parenting, health, relationships etc.

charity.charity_name: THE CRIDGE CENTRE FOR THE FAMILY
charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Kids Hearts and Minds Matter Project
charities.description: The Kids Hearts and Minds Matter Project seeks to expand free, trauma informed, counselling services to children who have experienced trauma, such as emotional or physical abuse, neglect, mistreatment or domestic violence. Services include tailored 1 on 1 or family counselling and support groups for parents/caregivers to give them tools and information to support their child.

charity.charity_name: CHILD ABUSE PREVENTION AND COUNSELLING SOCIETY OF GREATER VICTORIA
charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: SAFE Lifeline Program
charities.description: Eldercare Foundation strives to support seniors aging with dignity. Its SAFE Lifeline Program raises funds to provide medical alarm systems to low‐income seniors who wish to remain in their own homes (or need to as a result of limited openings in long‐term care) but require support to do so safely.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Food Programs
charities.description: Rainbow Kitchen seeks to address food security gaps, to reduce stigma and to be open to anyone. Its main program provides nutritious, tasty hot lunches each weekday ‐ no money charged, and no questions asked. Guests are invited to request a second portion of lunch to go, helping supplement their dinner or as a meal for a friend or family member. VRK has and is looking to expand their programs to meet other needs in the community.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Downtown Community Centre
charities.description: The Downtown Community Centre hosts a wide variety of free and inclusive healthy recreation and life skill programs for thousands of people in Victoria and elsewhere in the CRD. Programs operate every day with equipment and travel costs included, thereby removing the financial barriers. The DCC also supports the work of other diverse organizations (e.g. community/support groups, arts/sports organizations, and independent childcare providers) with low cost or free use of gymnasium, courtyard, kitchen and lobby spaces.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Youth Suicide Prevention and Support Programs
charities.description: The program works to educate, equip, and empower young people for better mental wellness, continued safety from suicide, and increased connectedness. It saves lives‐‐ getting youth timely help, engaging them in conversations about issues linked to shame and stigma, and making them aware that support is available through Youthspace.ca online counselling, Suicide Education and Awareness (SEA) workshops and Mindfulness for Middle Schools classroom sessions.

charity.charity_name: CRISIS INTERVENTION AND PUBLIC INFORMATION SOCIETY OF GREATER VICTORIA
charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Literacy Programs
charities.description: The Victoria Literacy Connection helps children, youth and adults improve their literacy skills, including reading, writing, and math, by providing tutoring and a variety of programs and workshops. Expanded future programming is anticipated to focus on media and financial literacy, as well as online service provision.

charity.charity_type: Advancement of Education

charities.name: Neighbourhood Hamper Delivery Program (NHDP)
charities.description: The Mustard Seed’s Neighbourhood Hamper Delivery Program exists to increase food security across the CRD by delivering food, in pre‐packed hampers, to 16 partner agencies (in multiple locations), serving 640 marginalized community members per month. Funds raised assist in program expansion to positively impact an additional 100 individuals each month.

charity.charity_type: Advancement of Religion

charities.name: Community Support Centre Programs
charities.description: Victoria Hospice offers bereavement services for caregivers, family members, and other members of the public who are experiencing grief and loss through their Community Support Centre. Funding will be used to increase counsellor hours, provide new programs such as support groups for those who have experienced a sudden traumatic loss or for those considering Medical Assistance in Death, and to increase in‐home support for patients and caregivers who are not able to reach services.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Sound of Change Initiative
charities.description: The IDHHC is dedicated to supporting Deaf, Deaf‐Blind, oral deaf, late deafened and hard of hearing individuals, families and communities. The Sound of Change Initiative provides free refurbished hearing aids, free hearing assessments, and personalized communication and aural rehabilitation supports to vulnerable and at‐risk populations, especially low‐income seniors and adults.

charity.charity_name: ISLAND DEAF AND HARD OF HEARING CENTRE ASSOCIATION
charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Radical Renovations Program
charities.description: Each year, HeroWork transforms other charities through its Radical Renovations projects. Renewing and expanding non‐profit community infrastructure can help charities make bigger impact, become more sustainable, lift up, and have a ripple effect in neighbourhoods where their important services are provided.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Youth Volunteer Programs
charities.description: Volunteer Victoria’s programs help youth understand their rights and obligations, explore their volunteering needs, experiment safely with options, and build a strategic volunteering plan so they can build their pre‐employment and employment skills, learn life skills, and find places to belong, add value, and be involved in community.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Breaking Down Barriers Program
charities.description: Breaking Down Barriers aims to educate and empower vulnerable community members with limited access to services who may be less be educated about their health care needs. Free workshops cover a range of topics with an intersectional lens including safer sex practices, contraception, how to access clinical services, and specialized programs.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Online Peer Support and Personal Recovery Space
charities.description: Looking Glass Foundation’s programs and services decrease isolation, instill hope, and sustain recovery for individuals across British Columbia who are impacted by eating disorders via free programs designed to meet individuals wherever they are in their recovery journey. Programs include a moderated online peer support group that meets 6 days a week and a moderated and confidential, digital forum that is accessible anytime.

charity.charity_name: LOOKING GLASS FOUNDATION FOR EATING DISORDERS
charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Field to Plate Initiative
charities.description:
The society facilitates the preservation of Greater Victoria farmland and the enhancement of food security to benefit current and future generations. Through unique partnerships with other not‐for‐profits, the Field to Plate Program is expanding to support growing, maintaining and donating organic produce from Newman Farm to food banks and local drop‐in centers to better serve Greater Victoria
persons in need – aiding in poverty relief and food insecurity.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Stigma-Free Zone School Program
charities.description: The Stigma‐Free Zone School Program uses school presenters to engage with students and encourage discussion about mental health and stigma as they share their personal story of living with, and managing mental illness. The program emphasizes that everyone has struggles but can lead extraordinary lives. It provides a takeaway Stigma‐Free Zone Rack Card that directs youth to resources and encourages them to continue the conversation with their parents and friends.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Pivot to Virtual Program
charities.description: The Pivot to Virtual Program will offer online facilitator‐led support and counselling strategies for anxiety, depression, and loneliness, etc. to groups of 10‐12 children/youth. Facilitators will engage participants, grouped by age, in virtual activities, role plays, mindfulness practices, art, and music geared towards helping individuals express their emotions, feel connected and supported. Parents can also take part in the virtual Triple P Parenting Course to learn core parenting skills and simple strategies to encourage positive behaviour, and prevent or manage misbehaviour, in their children.

charity.charity_name: SOUTH ISLAND CENTRE FOR COUNSELLING AND TRAINING SOCIETY
charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Victoria Peer Program
charities.description: Spinal Cord Injury BC’s Peer Support Program gives people in Greater Victoria with a spinal cord injury, their family and friends the opportunity to connect with others in similar situations, try activities they never imagined possible and continue learning about living well with an injury.

charity.charity_type: Other purposes beneficial to the community

charities.name: Garden Program
charities.description: The Shelbourne Community Kitchen provides a dignified and inclusive approach to building skills around growing and sourcing food, increasing access to nutritious, local produce, and providing meaningful volunteer opportunities to contribute to the physical and social well‐being of individuals and families living on low incomes. The Garden Program provides produce for Food Skills sessions and the Pantry (food bank). PECSF funding will be used to implement and refine a container gardening system, which will result in higher yields, less weeding and will be portable if/when the society moves to a new site.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: One-on-one direct volunteer services
charities.description: SVSS volunteers help their neighbours in a myriad of ways, from supportive transportation to a variety of medical and non‐medical appointments, companion visits, friendly calls, help with gardening and yard work, minor home repairs, shopping assistance, delivering food hampers, completing income tax returns, and many other activities associated with living independently in your own home.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Support Programs
charities.description: Autism BC seeks to empower, support and connect people on the autism spectrum and their families through education, training, resources and support groups towards promoting the health and inclusion of individuals with autism and related conditions in the region.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Student Programs
charities.description: Through partnerships with educators and volunteers from local businesses, JABC offers important interactive, hands-on learning experiences in financial literacy, entrepreneurship, and work readiness to students in Grades 4 to 12 in all communities across the Cariboo region.

charities.name: Spinal Cord Injury BC - Peer Support Program
charities.description: Spinal Cord Injury BC’s Peer Support Program gives people in the region with a spinal cord injury, their family and friends the opportunity to connect with others in similar situations, try activities they never imagined possible and continue learning about living well with an injury.

region.name: Metro Vancouver
region.notes: NV - 19OCT2021 - Region 027 name change from Greater Vancouver to Metro Vancouver.

charities.name: Support Programs
charities.description: Autism BC Programs seek to empower, support and connect people in the Greater Vancouver region on the autism spectrum and their families through education, training, resources and support groups towards promoting the health and inclusion of individuals with autism and related conditions.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Service Dog Program
charities.description: BC Guide Dogs endeavors to change the lives of individuals who are blind/visually impaired, children with profound autism, and/or Veterans, RCMP and First Responders living with an Operational Stress Injury/Post‐Traumatic Stress Disorder by providing professionally trained Guide Dogs, Autism Service Dogs and PTSD Service Dogs. Staff prepare the dogs through specialized training, they match and train the clients with their dogs, and provide follow‐up.

charity.charity_type: Advancement of Education

charities.name: Big Brothers Community Program
charities.description: The Big Brothers Community Program has been proven to increase children’s happiness, connection to their community, and future success. The program matches “Littles” – children and youth who are in need of a positive adult role model – with volunteer “Bigs”. Each match spends two to four hours of quality time together each week, building their friendship through sports, shared hobbies, cultural activities, or just talking together.

charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Big Sisters Mentoring Program
charities.description: The Big Sisters Mentoring Program is a one‐to‐one mentorship for Little Sisters (ages 7 to 17) that enables life‐changing relationships to ignite the power and potential of young people. Once a week for a minimum of one year, the mentor and the Little Sister meet and develop a relationship built on trust and common interests. Both are supported by experienced caseworkers.

charity.charity_name: BIG SISTERS OF B.C. LOWER MAINLAND
charity.charity_type: Relief of Poverty

charities.name: Crabtree Corner Community Resource Centre
charities.description: The YWCA Crabtree Corner is a place of warmth, support and refuge in the Downtown Eastside, where marginalized women and families can access holistic services critical to their health, healing and independence. Crabtree Corner is open year‐round, Monday to Friday, with programs and services delivered throughout the day. Services include food security programming, support for single mothers and family programming.

charity.charity_type: Advancement of Religion

charities.name: Youth Suicide Prevention Program
charities.description: The Youth Suicide Prevention Program is evidence‐based and recognizes that suicide is a complicated, multi‐faceted issue that must be approached holistically. The Crisis Centre’s comprehensive approach begins at the grassroots level, working to reduce the stigma surrounding suicide in our communities, helping youth at their most vulnerable times of distress, and creating a strong network of ready, willing and able community members who can recognize suicide and work to build safety from suicide.
